1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Subtitles by KBS World

2
00:00:04,750 --> 00:00:06,210
Where's Gwangbak?

3
00:00:06,220 --> 00:00:08,540
We went out early to do research.

4
00:00:08,560 --> 00:00:12,340
She's not going to debut as a writer this year.

5
00:00:12,350 --> 00:00:15,640
She's all bluff, like someone I know.

6
00:00:15,650 --> 00:00:18,440
Just say she's like me.

7
00:00:18,460 --> 00:00:20,240
Don't beat around the bush.

8
00:00:20,250 --> 00:00:22,950
But you still understood.

9
00:00:23,350 --> 00:00:27,440
Mom, the soy bean stew is extra delicious.

10
00:00:27,460 --> 00:00:29,420
I didn't know it was this good.

11
00:00:29,430 --> 00:00:31,320
That means you're old.

12
00:00:31,320 --> 00:00:32,990
How could you say that?

13
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:34,340
Do I look old?

14
00:00:34,350 --> 00:00:36,250
Everyone thinks I look younger than I am.

15
00:00:36,260 --> 00:00:37,150
No way.

16
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:40,580
You're all bluff, too!

17
00:00:40,590 --> 00:00:42,080
I'm not!

18
00:00:42,090 --> 00:00:45,610
You bluffed about finding a woman for him!

19
00:00:45,620 --> 00:00:47,880
I've been asking around, so hold on.

20
00:00:47,900 --> 00:00:49,390
Just forget it!

21
00:00:49,400 --> 00:00:52,720
I'll die before that happens.

22
00:00:52,730 --> 00:00:55,620
You have to be careful setting people up.

23
00:00:55,620 --> 00:00:59,680
It's not like he has anything to offer.

24
00:00:59,700 --> 00:01:01,340
Yes, he does!

25
00:01:01,350 --> 00:01:03,910
You're embarrassing me, mom.

26
00:01:03,930 --> 00:01:06,820
He works part time and makes money,

27
00:01:06,820 --> 00:01:10,280
and he's learning how to make pizza

28
00:01:10,290 --> 00:01:12,810
so he can open a pizza shop.

29
00:01:12,820 --> 00:01:15,580
I'm not expecting much for a daughter in law.

30
00:01:15,590 --> 00:01:19,840
I just want someone who won't cut me off

31
00:01:19,850 --> 00:01:22,910
and drive me crazy whenever I talk.

32
00:01:22,930 --> 00:01:24,590
Don't beat around the bush.

33
00:01:24,590 --> 00:01:27,140
You want someone who's not like me.

34
00:01:27,150 --> 00:01:29,280
You understood, so I'm good.

35
00:01:29,290 --> 00:01:30,840
Grandmother, you're just as bad.

36
00:01:30,850 --> 00:01:32,640
You say whatever you want to say.

37
00:01:32,650 --> 00:01:34,780
I'm a descendant of the six martyrs.

38
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:37,890
I say what needs to be said, no matter what.

39
00:01:37,900 --> 00:01:39,190
I know.

40
00:01:41,960 --> 00:01:45,190
You must work at a nice place.

41
00:01:45,190 --> 00:01:46,990
You can come and go as you wish.

42
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:48,740
Of course.

43
00:01:48,750 --> 00:01:51,180
What my mom just said...

44
00:01:51,190 --> 00:01:53,810
I know. I'll find someone.

45
00:01:53,830 --> 00:01:55,420
I don't care about anything else.

46
00:01:55,430 --> 00:01:58,450
I know, money.

47
00:01:58,460 --> 00:02:00,950
I'm not totally crazy about money,

48
00:02:00,960 --> 00:02:02,390
but because of where I am right now,

49
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:05,920
it would be nicer if she had some money.

50
00:02:05,930 --> 00:02:08,550
I don't care about the looks. You know?

51
00:02:08,560 --> 00:02:10,050
I said I got it!

52
00:02:10,060 --> 00:02:14,290
If she's rich, she could be an old hag.

53
00:02:15,060 --> 00:02:16,520
I'm not that desperate.

54
00:02:19,650 --> 00:02:20,950
Oh, my!

55
00:02:20,960 --> 00:02:22,750
Hello.

56
00:02:22,750 --> 00:02:24,380
Excuse me?

57
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:26,790
You must be doing really well.

58
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:29,790
You look better than when you lived at my house.

59
00:02:30,530 --> 00:02:32,110
Who...

60
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:35,310
You don't remember?
I was your landlady.

61
00:02:36,460 --> 00:02:37,690
Oh...

62
00:02:37,690 --> 00:02:40,740
You don't fight with your husband anymore?

63
00:02:40,750 --> 00:02:43,110
You used to fight with him and cry.

64
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:45,390
I don't cry anymore.

65
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:46,640
Bye.

66
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:50,020
Hey, Mrs. Landlady!

67
00:02:50,620 --> 00:02:52,340
I'm not married!

68
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:54,520
Don't call me "Mrs."
How annoying.

69
00:02:54,530 --> 00:02:56,890
You said you're single, right?

70
00:02:56,900 --> 00:02:59,490
I am, so?

71
00:02:59,750 --> 00:03:01,020
Goodbye.

72
00:03:01,330 --> 00:03:02,790
Friend!

73
00:03:04,030 --> 00:03:05,140
What brings you here?

74
00:03:05,150 --> 00:03:06,890
I came to see you.

75
00:03:08,030 --> 00:03:11,850
Wow, you must be making lots of money.

76
00:03:11,860 --> 00:03:12,750
Where's Yeongdal?

77
00:03:12,750 --> 00:03:14,280
She went out to meet up with a friend.

78
00:03:14,300 --> 00:03:16,150
You don't want Yeongdal to get married?

79
00:03:16,150 --> 00:03:17,810
I do.

80
00:03:17,830 --> 00:03:21,190
It's difficult to choose from all those men.

81
00:03:21,190 --> 00:03:24,880
What kind of son in law do you want?

82
00:03:24,900 --> 00:03:28,320
Someone rich and handsome with a good job.

83
00:03:28,330 --> 00:03:29,990
And he must be good to me.

84
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:33,420
My Don is handsome, yes.

85
00:03:33,430 --> 00:03:35,920
But he has no money.

86
00:03:35,930 --> 00:03:39,550
He has no future and he has a part time job.

87
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:41,610
What kind of daughter in law do you want?

88
00:03:41,620 --> 00:03:44,010
I don't want much.

89
00:03:44,020 --> 00:03:47,080
If Yeongdal says yes, I'll consider her.

90
00:03:47,100 --> 00:03:49,020
What?

91
00:03:49,020 --> 00:03:51,640
You'll consider her?

92
00:03:51,660 --> 00:03:53,220
I don't believe this.

93
00:03:53,230 --> 00:03:55,850
Don't say that!
Loser has nothing to offer!

94
00:03:55,860 --> 00:03:58,820
Goof off's nothing special, but he got Hobak.

95
00:03:58,820 --> 00:04:02,880
If Don marries Yeongdal, we'd be even.

96
00:04:02,890 --> 00:04:04,880
How dare you!

97
00:04:04,890 --> 00:04:07,280
Don't even think about that.

98
00:04:07,300 --> 00:04:09,090
I want you to leave!

99
00:04:09,100 --> 00:04:10,890
And I don't want to be friends with you!

100
00:04:10,890 --> 00:04:11,990
Don't push me.

101
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:16,450
If you act like that, your daughter's going to get old and die alone!

102
00:04:16,450 --> 00:04:18,310
What? Leave!

103
00:04:18,320 --> 00:04:19,710
Hey!

104
00:04:21,390 --> 00:04:24,280
And don't come back!

105
00:04:24,300 --> 00:04:26,420
The Korean War was nothing compared to this!

106
00:04:26,430 --> 00:04:28,310
Egh, hyo, hyo, hyo, hyo.

107
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:34,720
Oh my!

108
00:04:36,430 --> 00:04:38,420
You're full of energy, aren't you?

109
00:04:38,430 --> 00:04:40,390
We're lucky that gate isn't broken.

110
00:04:40,390 --> 00:04:43,240
This is all your fault.

111
00:04:43,250 --> 00:04:44,350
What is?

112
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:47,790
You treat Don like dirt, so everyone else does!

113
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:50,810
Anggeum, I fixed the stroller.

114
00:04:50,820 --> 00:04:55,140
Hey, don't say hi to the beauty salon woman.

115
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:56,850
Don't even talk to her when you see her.

116
00:04:56,860 --> 00:04:59,590
Tell her to keep her stupid daughter!

117
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:03,050
I should just die!
Egh, hyo, hyo, hyo!

118
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:07,240
She must have asked her for her daughter.

119
00:05:07,250 --> 00:05:09,790
Don, don't even think about it.

120
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:11,850
I don't want her.

121
00:05:11,860 --> 00:05:14,720
I couldn't, if I wanted.

122
00:05:14,730 --> 00:05:16,050
What?

123
00:05:16,060 --> 00:05:18,590
Nothing. I fixed the stroller.

124
00:05:28,100 --> 00:05:28,850
Hey.

125
00:05:28,860 --> 00:05:31,550
Uncle, are you free tonight?

126
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:33,550
Really?

127
00:05:33,560 --> 00:05:35,720
Who is it?

128
00:05:35,730 --> 00:05:37,420
Is she pretty?

129
00:05:37,430 --> 00:05:39,720
I thought you didn't care.

130
00:05:39,730 --> 00:05:41,320
Just meet her.

131
00:05:41,320 --> 00:05:43,490
She's a semi real estate tycoon.

132
00:05:46,020 --> 00:05:48,840
Semi real estate tycoon?

133
00:05:48,860 --> 00:05:50,150
Why would she want me?

134
00:05:56,750 --> 00:05:58,140
This isn't working.

135
00:06:06,620 --> 00:06:08,610
This is nutty, nutty, nuts.

136
00:06:17,860 --> 00:06:19,240
Dad!

137
00:06:19,250 --> 00:06:20,880
Boys!

138
00:06:20,890 --> 00:06:23,740
- It's dad!
- Dad! Dad!

139
00:06:23,750 --> 00:06:25,440
What's wrong with you guys?

140
00:06:25,820 --> 00:06:27,740
It's been so long, they're happy to see you.

141
00:06:27,750 --> 00:06:28,850
What are you doing home?

142
00:06:28,860 --> 00:06:30,290
Mom, why are you home?

143
00:06:30,300 --> 00:06:33,150
I had to close the shop for your kids.

144
00:06:33,160 --> 00:06:35,550
Hobak asked me to take care of them.

145
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:36,940
I'm making spicy rice cakes.

146
00:06:36,950 --> 00:06:39,880
I don't want that!
I want dad's pizza.

147
00:06:39,890 --> 00:06:41,280
Pizza! Pizza!

148
00:06:43,190 --> 00:06:44,880
Dad, have some!

149
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:47,810
I don't like this kind of food.

150
00:06:47,820 --> 00:06:51,380
I'm more of a rice and kimchi kind of man.

151
00:06:52,950 --> 00:06:55,110
Sintong, Bangtong.

152
00:06:56,930 --> 00:06:58,590
This is just a "what if."

153
00:06:59,300 --> 00:07:03,020
If we were to live without mom...

154
00:07:05,730 --> 00:07:07,720
I can't even talk to you!

155
00:07:07,730 --> 00:07:10,450
I'm not even finished yet!

156
00:07:10,450 --> 00:07:13,610
I miss mom so much!

157
00:07:13,620 --> 00:07:15,640
Why would you say that?

158
00:07:16,190 --> 00:07:19,110
I said "if."

159
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:22,640
If mom doesn't come back from her trip...

160
00:07:22,660 --> 00:07:27,320
- Mom!
- Mom!

161
00:07:27,320 --> 00:07:30,210
How can you cry at the word "mom"?

162
00:07:30,230 --> 00:07:32,020
Man!

163
00:07:32,020 --> 00:07:34,280
Why are you crying?

164
00:07:36,500 --> 00:07:38,650
Why did you make them cry?

165
00:07:38,660 --> 00:07:41,610
They started crying when I said the word "mom."

166
00:07:41,620 --> 00:07:44,010
It's like they're orphans or something.

167
00:07:44,020 --> 00:07:46,990
At their age, they need their mom.

168
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:51,510
They don't even want to eat right now.

169
00:07:51,520 --> 00:07:53,990
Who goes on a business trip just like that?

170
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:55,650
Mom.

171
00:07:56,450 --> 00:07:59,280
Do you have any money?

172
00:07:59,290 --> 00:08:01,280
Money? How much?

173
00:08:01,290 --> 00:08:02,140
$100,000?

174
00:08:02,150 --> 00:08:03,180
What?

175
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:04,850
I wish I did!

176
00:08:04,860 --> 00:08:07,420
How can I have $100,000?

177
00:08:07,420 --> 00:08:09,180
You can't borrow it?

178
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:12,950
I don't know anyone who's that rich!

179
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:14,950
Why? Why do you need it?

180
00:08:15,790 --> 00:08:17,440
I need it for something.

181
00:08:17,460 --> 00:08:19,420
What about your rich director?

182
00:08:19,420 --> 00:08:20,940
Why don't you ask her?

183
00:08:27,830 --> 00:08:29,290
Man!

184
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:38,320
This isn't working.

185
00:08:39,390 --> 00:08:41,610
I think he gave up.

186
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:45,010
He didn't.

187
00:08:45,020 --> 00:08:46,990
He's trying to get the money.

188
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:49,040
Please give him more time.

189
00:09:01,860 --> 00:09:03,240
I'm bored.

190
00:09:03,250 --> 00:09:05,380
Is there anything fun we can do?

191
00:09:06,500 --> 00:09:08,350
Do you want to play go stop?

192
00:09:09,020 --> 00:09:10,380
That's lame.

193
00:09:10,390 --> 00:09:12,040
Do you know how to play cards?

194
00:09:12,050 --> 00:09:13,210
No.

195
00:09:13,650 --> 00:09:14,640
How about chess?

196
00:09:14,650 --> 00:09:16,380
No.

197
00:09:16,390 --> 00:09:19,010
Can you dance the waltz?

198
00:09:19,020 --> 00:09:20,680
Let's just play go stop, okay?

199
00:09:20,700 --> 00:09:22,610
I'll teach you.

200
00:09:22,620 --> 00:09:26,040
Once you get into it, you'll never stop.

201
00:09:26,050 --> 00:09:30,550
A few coins can give you loads of fun when you play go stop.

202
00:09:30,550 --> 00:09:31,810
No thanks.

203
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:37,350
Oh, this is nuts.

204
00:09:42,460 --> 00:09:48,350
[Only the first place can be Choi Daese's daughter in law]

205
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:53,410
Four people got eliminated on the way.

206
00:09:53,420 --> 00:09:54,840
I'm so nervous.

207
00:09:55,390 --> 00:09:57,880
Get in one line!

208
00:09:57,890 --> 00:10:01,410
We'll move to the dorms!

209
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:12,150
Let's go.

210
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:25,320
Change into the uniforms and gather outside.

211
00:10:44,650 --> 00:10:46,720
Huh? Where did the luggage go?

212
00:11:00,500 --> 00:11:01,880
Mom, what is it?

213
00:11:01,890 --> 00:11:03,180
Where are you?

214
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:05,850
Why did you take the luggage?

215
00:11:05,860 --> 00:11:07,640
I told you,

216
00:11:07,650 --> 00:11:09,510
I'm going on a trip with my friends.

217
00:11:09,520 --> 00:11:11,740
You never said that!

218
00:11:11,750 --> 00:11:14,190
You're not in that audition, are you?

219
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:18,320
Assemble!

220
00:11:19,050 --> 00:11:20,440
I got to go, mom!

221
00:11:20,700 --> 00:11:22,950
Listen carefully.

222
00:11:22,960 --> 00:11:26,610
All your personal information will be sealed.

223
00:11:26,620 --> 00:11:29,610
You'll be addressed by your number.

224
00:11:29,620 --> 00:11:32,850
Here are the rules to the audition.

225
00:11:32,860 --> 00:11:37,290
You will take five tests, and for each test,

226
00:11:37,290 --> 00:11:41,380
the two lowest scores will be eliminated.

227
00:11:41,390 --> 00:11:44,040
And in the final round, test number 5,

228
00:11:44,050 --> 00:11:46,080
only one person will be picked.

229
00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:48,820
We don't need 2nd or 3rd places.

230
00:11:48,830 --> 00:11:51,090
We only need the 1st place winner.

231
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:54,090
There can only be one daughter in law.

232
00:11:56,230 --> 00:11:58,190
The contents of the tests are top secret.

233
00:11:58,200 --> 00:12:00,090
You all must pay close attention.

234
00:12:10,830 --> 00:12:13,590
[Choi Daese's daughter in law audition]

235
00:12:31,100 --> 00:12:33,050
Are you kidding me with this?

236
00:12:33,050 --> 00:12:34,910
They can't be normal.

237
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:38,210
They probably came for the pay.

238
00:12:38,230 --> 00:12:41,240
I can't believe you're doing this.

239
00:12:41,250 --> 00:12:42,090
Just watch.

240
00:12:42,100 --> 00:12:45,850
I'm going to eliminate that rude girl.

241
00:12:45,860 --> 00:12:47,990
How dare she do this to me?

242
00:12:52,390 --> 00:12:54,350
Let's go! Let's go!

243
00:12:54,360 --> 00:12:56,790
- Hey!
- Let's go! Let's go!

244
00:13:00,620 --> 00:13:01,740
Hey!

245
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:10,280
Yes! Yes!

246
00:13:11,500 --> 00:13:13,140
Let's go!

247
00:13:16,420 --> 00:13:18,440
Oh, Jangbi!

248
00:13:18,460 --> 00:13:19,890
look at her! Look!

249
00:13:19,890 --> 00:13:22,780
She did this! Whoa!

250
00:13:32,360 --> 00:13:33,920
Look at her!

251
00:13:38,550 --> 00:13:39,680
Let's go!

252
00:13:39,700 --> 00:13:41,610
Let's go, number 1!

253
00:13:49,920 --> 00:13:51,140
Man...

254
00:13:55,620 --> 00:13:57,240
Woohoo!

255
00:13:58,330 --> 00:14:00,450
That was a warm up.

256
00:14:00,460 --> 00:14:03,720
The real audition will start back at the school.

257
00:14:03,730 --> 00:14:05,350
Warm up?

258
00:14:05,730 --> 00:14:08,490
This wasn't part of the test.

259
00:14:08,500 --> 00:14:10,720
You should've told me that!

260
00:14:10,730 --> 00:14:13,450
I thought this was a test so I gave it my all!

261
00:14:13,460 --> 00:14:15,220
That sucks.

262
00:14:15,230 --> 00:14:17,350
I can't believe this!

263
00:14:17,360 --> 00:14:18,740
I'm leaving!

264
00:14:20,420 --> 00:14:21,940
I don't want that!

265
00:14:27,960 --> 00:14:30,390
Jangbi, I like her.

266
00:14:30,390 --> 00:14:32,510
We're not looking for your wife.

267
00:14:32,520 --> 00:14:35,810
She's proud and passionate.

268
00:14:35,830 --> 00:14:38,690
You want a daughter in law like her?

269
00:14:38,700 --> 00:14:43,890
Isn't the rude girl also proud and passionate?

270
00:14:43,890 --> 00:14:44,990
Man.

271
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:49,380
See? You actually like girls like her.

272
00:14:49,390 --> 00:14:50,610
Don't even joke about it.

273
00:14:50,620 --> 00:14:52,990
I hate rude girls.

274
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,410
Man...

275
00:14:55,120 --> 00:14:59,190
The first test is on basic knowledge.

276
00:15:03,520 --> 00:15:05,310
[Choi Daese's daughter in law audition Crossword Puzzle Test]

277
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:33,410
I'm too weak, and I lost my appetite.

278
00:15:33,420 --> 00:15:34,710
Anggeum, this is for you.

