00:33:14,020 --> 00:33:15,880
Look, Mr. Park,

558
00:33:15,900 --> 00:33:19,690
you said you'd take care of it!

559
00:33:19,700 --> 00:33:22,240
I must have some inheritance.

560
00:33:22,250 --> 00:33:26,610
I want it now and you can't do it?

561
00:33:26,630 --> 00:33:28,920
I'm not going to the board meeting.

562
00:33:28,930 --> 00:33:32,950
If you keep this up, I'm taking legal measures.

563
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:48,080
I drew you a bath.

564
00:33:48,090 --> 00:33:49,180
Dad,

565
00:33:49,190 --> 00:33:52,410
I don't want to talk to you anymore.

566
00:33:52,420 --> 00:33:54,640
I'll go through the lawyer.

567
00:33:54,650 --> 00:33:58,580
Just do what my lawyer, Mr. Park tells you to do.

568
00:33:58,590 --> 00:34:00,620
Your bath..

569
00:34:00,630 --> 00:34:02,040
I don't want anything else.

570
00:34:02,050 --> 00:34:05,140
I just want what's rightfully mine right now.

571
00:34:06,360 --> 00:34:08,540
But that's not yours!

572
00:34:08,550 --> 00:34:12,810
Grandfather left it to me!

573
00:34:13,920 --> 00:34:15,910
I'm not going back to the States.

574
00:34:15,920 --> 00:34:17,490
I said no!

575
00:34:17,500 --> 00:34:19,250
Your bath...

576
00:34:19,960 --> 00:34:21,720
What's wrong with you?

577
00:34:22,820 --> 00:34:25,390
Dad, talk to my lawyer.

578
00:34:26,420 --> 00:34:28,240
Can't you see I'm busy?

579
00:34:28,260 --> 00:34:30,250
Why are you talking about the stupid bath?

580
00:34:30,260 --> 00:34:32,720
How can you hold down a job, being so dense?

581
00:34:32,730 --> 00:34:36,080
Can't you see I'm talking to my dad?

582
00:34:36,090 --> 00:34:38,810
I can't see anything right now...

583
00:34:39,500 --> 00:34:40,720
I'm going out.

584
00:34:42,690 --> 00:34:44,380
Hey, hey...

585
00:34:47,130 --> 00:34:48,890
This is nuts.

586
00:34:52,420 --> 00:34:54,540
- Hey, Sedal!
- Oh, hey.

587
00:34:54,550 --> 00:34:55,620
It's been a while.

588
00:34:55,630 --> 00:34:57,810
What's up?
I heard you were busy.

589
00:34:57,820 --> 00:34:59,620
Let's play some golf, okay?

590
00:34:59,630 --> 00:35:01,450
Let's go next week.

591
00:35:01,460 --> 00:35:02,950
Do you have some time?

592
00:35:02,960 --> 00:35:04,620
Yes. You want coffee?

593
00:35:04,630 --> 00:35:07,220
Or let's get dinner a little later.

594
00:35:07,230 --> 00:35:09,250
I don't have time for that.

595
00:35:09,260 --> 00:35:13,650
I'm in a hurry.
Can you lend me money?

596
00:35:13,650 --> 00:35:14,340
Money?

597
00:35:14,360 --> 00:35:16,120
Yes, can you lend me $100,000?

598
00:35:16,130 --> 00:35:18,580
Oh, I have to finish writing a report.

599
00:35:18,590 --> 00:35:20,410
Hey, Goof off, call me later, okay?

600
00:35:20,420 --> 00:35:21,510
Hey...

601
00:35:32,650 --> 00:35:34,040
Hey, Goof off.

602
00:35:34,050 --> 00:35:35,410
Hi.

603
00:35:35,420 --> 00:35:38,380
Are you busy?
Can we get coffee?

604
00:35:38,400 --> 00:35:41,490
I know why you're here.

605
00:35:41,500 --> 00:35:42,250
What?

606
00:35:42,260 --> 00:35:44,220
These days,

607
00:35:44,230 --> 00:35:46,680
it only takes a minute for word to spread.

608
00:35:46,690 --> 00:35:48,240
It's an amazing world.

609
00:35:48,260 --> 00:35:52,050
Everyone's talking about you needing money.

610
00:35:53,130 --> 00:35:54,750
I was going to ignore you,

611
00:35:54,760 --> 00:35:57,190
but I thought I should give you some advice.

612
00:35:57,190 --> 00:35:59,640
I heard you hooked up with a rich woman.

613
00:35:59,650 --> 00:36:03,410
You abandoned your wife and kids?

614
00:36:03,420 --> 00:36:06,340
We don't think you're worth our time.

615
00:36:06,360 --> 00:36:09,420
For money?
What you did is unspeakable.

616
00:36:09,420 --> 00:36:11,490
Why do you need to borrow money?

617
00:36:11,500 --> 00:36:13,350
She ran out of money?

618
00:36:14,050 --> 00:36:16,990
Why don't you sell that watch?

619
00:36:20,150 --> 00:36:21,340
Wake up!

620
00:36:29,260 --> 00:36:31,520
[Pawn Shop]

621
00:36:50,900 --> 00:36:52,720
How much can you give me?

622
00:36:54,090 --> 00:36:56,390
how much do you want?

623
00:36:56,400 --> 00:36:58,350
I'd like $50,000,

624
00:36:58,360 --> 00:37:01,080
but I'll take whatever you can give me.

625
00:37:02,650 --> 00:37:04,720
It's not an average watch,

626
00:37:04,730 --> 00:37:06,620
so don't put it with other watches.

627
00:37:06,630 --> 00:37:08,080
And don't show it to anyone.

628
00:37:08,090 --> 00:37:10,080
I'll come back for it in a week.

629
00:37:10,090 --> 00:37:12,280
Did you buy this?

630
00:37:12,800 --> 00:37:14,520
I didn't really buy it.

631
00:37:14,530 --> 00:37:15,850
It was a gift?

632
00:37:15,860 --> 00:37:17,250
Yes.

633
00:37:17,260 --> 00:37:19,020
From a woman?

634
00:37:19,030 --> 00:37:20,250
Of course.

635
00:37:23,690 --> 00:37:25,240
Why?

636
00:37:26,190 --> 00:37:30,040
You should keep this instead of selling it.

637
00:37:30,900 --> 00:37:32,020
What?

638
00:37:34,530 --> 00:37:36,820
I can't cook.

639
00:37:36,820 --> 00:37:38,310
Me neither.

640
00:37:38,320 --> 00:37:40,240
No one here can cook well.

641
00:37:40,260 --> 00:37:42,190
Everyone's the same.

642
00:37:42,960 --> 00:37:44,850
I wish the contest was to eat this radish.

643
00:37:47,800 --> 00:37:50,220
Let's start by eating the radish.

644
00:37:50,230 --> 00:37:51,750
Really?

645
00:38:06,630 --> 00:38:08,020
Number 4 won 1st place!

646
00:38:09,820 --> 00:38:11,680
That was warm up.

647
00:38:15,730 --> 00:38:17,310
- Darn it!
- Okay.

648
00:38:17,320 --> 00:38:19,140
This is the fourth test.

649
00:38:19,150 --> 00:38:21,990
The cooking test you've been waiting for!

650
00:38:22,000 --> 00:38:26,290
Your parents in law came to your house,

651
00:38:26,300 --> 00:38:29,650
and you must whip something up in a hurry.

652
00:38:29,650 --> 00:38:33,740
We have some common ingredients up here.

653
00:38:33,760 --> 00:38:36,190
You can take anything you want.

654
00:38:36,190 --> 00:38:42,910
Mr. Choi Daese who's holding this audition will be the judge of this test.

655
00:38:42,920 --> 00:38:46,040
You have 30 minutes.

656
00:39:22,000 --> 00:39:23,890
Things are not going well.

657
00:39:23,900 --> 00:39:27,750
She only did well on the first test.

658
00:39:27,760 --> 00:39:30,390
Other girls are pretty good at cooking, 

659
00:39:30,400 --> 00:39:32,790
but Number 4 is not so good.

660
00:39:32,800 --> 00:39:35,020
Can I ask you to do something for me?

661
00:39:35,630 --> 00:39:36,720
I have some.

662
00:39:36,730 --> 00:39:38,850
We brought some for ourselves.

663
00:39:40,920 --> 00:39:42,080
Okay.

664
00:39:44,530 --> 00:39:45,990
Oh, stir fried fish cake.

665
00:39:46,000 --> 00:39:47,390
That looks really good.

666
00:39:47,920 --> 00:39:50,680
Are you sure that's edible?

667
00:39:53,730 --> 00:39:55,490
Oh!

668
00:39:56,800 --> 00:39:57,990
What's this?

669
00:39:58,000 --> 00:39:59,350
Soft tofu stew.

670
00:40:06,150 --> 00:40:08,040
Oh, this smells good.

671
00:40:08,050 --> 00:40:10,350
This looks very edible to me.

672
00:40:10,360 --> 00:40:11,810
Can I have some water?

673
00:40:11,820 --> 00:40:13,010
Of course.

674
00:40:22,030 --> 00:40:24,250
- Here it is.
- Thank you.

675
00:41:02,650 --> 00:41:05,880
Please stand in front of your dish.

676
00:41:11,050 --> 00:41:12,620
Check your rankings.

677
00:41:20,690 --> 00:41:22,540
1st place!

678
00:41:26,690 --> 00:41:28,880
1st place! 1st place! 1st place!

679
00:41:33,690 --> 00:41:36,680
Seven people remain.

680
00:41:36,690 --> 00:41:39,950
Only the final test remains.

681
00:41:39,960 --> 00:41:43,390
But the points given are the highest,

682
00:41:44,190 --> 00:41:46,910
so we don't know who will win.

683
00:41:49,260 --> 00:41:50,320
Oh...

684
00:41:59,260 --> 00:42:00,450
Man...

685
00:42:06,090 --> 00:42:07,540
Since everyone looks finished,

686
00:42:07,550 --> 00:42:11,280
I think we should have a family meeting.

687
00:42:11,300 --> 00:42:12,490
Family meeting?

688
00:42:12,500 --> 00:42:14,390
Why not? Let's do it.

689
00:42:14,400 --> 00:42:16,720
But what would you have to say here?

690
00:42:16,730 --> 00:42:19,310
Why not? He's family.

691
00:42:19,960 --> 00:42:21,620
Actually,

692
00:42:21,630 --> 00:42:24,450
I want everyone to help with the chores.

693
00:42:26,090 --> 00:42:27,620
Oh...

694
00:42:27,630 --> 00:42:29,450
This is a big family,

695
00:42:29,460 --> 00:42:33,720
but we all depend on mother alone.

696
00:42:33,730 --> 00:42:36,490
She does everything for us.

697
00:42:36,500 --> 00:42:40,720
From things like cooking, laundry, cleaning

698
00:42:40,730 --> 00:42:42,450
to taking care of Aeji and Jungji.

699
00:42:43,460 --> 00:42:46,410
I know it's my fault,

700
00:42:46,420 --> 00:42:49,740
but I'm afraid mother will get sick.

701
00:42:51,400 --> 00:42:54,520
People in the past did more!

702
00:42:54,530 --> 00:42:56,220
Grandmother, stop saying that.

703
00:42:56,230 --> 00:42:59,250
You always talk about the past.

704
00:42:59,260 --> 00:43:01,520
Minjung is right.

705
00:43:01,530 --> 00:43:04,390
We should've done this a long time ago.

706
00:43:04,400 --> 00:43:07,990
Mother, she's no spring chicken.

707
00:43:08,000 --> 00:43:09,450
She's old, she's over 60 years old.

708
00:43:09,460 --> 00:43:11,540
Being over 60 years old isn't old!

709
00:43:11,550 --> 00:43:13,510
She's in her prime!

710
00:43:13,530 --> 00:43:16,290
You were born healthy,

711
00:43:16,300 --> 00:43:18,520
so you're healthier than I am right now,

712
00:43:18,530 --> 00:43:21,450
but I'm not like you.

713
00:43:21,460 --> 00:43:23,350
I'm scared of everything I have to do.

714
00:43:23,360 --> 00:43:27,220
Then we should decide what to do.

715
00:43:27,230 --> 00:43:29,390
Mother, what do you think?

716
00:43:29,400 --> 00:43:31,850
What should we do?

717
00:43:31,860 --> 00:43:34,620
Can I tell you what I thought of?

718
00:43:34,630 --> 00:43:36,040
Sure, go ahead.

719
00:43:36,050 --> 00:43:38,580
Mother can continue to cook.

720
00:43:38,590 --> 00:43:41,620
She is the best cook here.

721
00:43:41,630 --> 00:43:45,290
And I think we should divide up the rest.

722
00:43:45,300 --> 00:43:51,090
We can take turns doing the dishes and doing the laundry.

723
00:43:51,090 --> 00:43:54,280
Uncle can clean downstairs,

724
00:43:54,300 --> 00:43:58,520
and I can clean upstairs.

725
00:43:58,530 --> 00:43:59,990
The front yard,

726
00:44:00,000 --> 00:44:03,250
I think the men can clean it on Sundays.

727
00:44:03,260 --> 00:44:08,120
Oh, that would be amazing help for me.

728
00:44:08,500 --> 00:44:12,290
Then make a schedule and post it up there.

729
00:44:12,300 --> 00:44:13,990
Haebak, you do it.

730
00:44:14,000 --> 00:44:14,950
Okay.

731
00:44:14,960 --> 00:44:17,490
The breakfast dishes can be done by

732
00:44:17,500 --> 00:44:21,950
grandmother, uncle and Subak.

733
00:44:21,960 --> 00:44:23,250
Me too?

734
00:44:23,260 --> 00:44:26,120
Of course. You're very healthy.

735
00:44:26,130 --> 00:44:28,750
Father, Daebak and I'll do the dinner dishes.

736
00:44:28,760 --> 00:44:32,550
And Minjung can do them on Sundays, since you get off late.

737
00:44:32,550 --> 00:44:34,450
Father, when should we start?

738
00:44:34,460 --> 00:44:36,750
We should start this evening.

739
00:44:36,760 --> 00:44:40,790
That means you have to go first.

740
00:44:40,800 --> 00:44:42,320
Okay.

741
00:44:42,320 --> 00:44:43,990
I'll start it off.

742
00:44:44,000 --> 00:44:46,520
I don't believe this!

743
00:44:46,530 --> 00:44:50,450
I have to watch him do the dishes now?

744
00:44:50,460 --> 00:44:54,120
You're having a hard time because of your kids!

745
00:44:54,130 --> 00:44:55,950
When my father gets discharged,

746
00:44:55,960 --> 00:44:57,620
I'll come home early and look after Jungji.

747
00:44:57,630 --> 00:44:59,310
You pick the time, too.

748
00:44:59,320 --> 00:45:02,080
She's not doing it for free. I pay her.

749
00:45:02,090 --> 00:45:04,040
It's not about the money.

750
00:45:04,050 --> 00:45:06,280
We should talk about this.

751
00:45:06,300 --> 00:45:10,750
You keep saying you pay me, but how much

752
00:45:10,760 --> 00:45:14,390
have you paid me? $100 twice, $200 once.

753
00:45:14,400 --> 00:45:18,250
I only got $400 from you. $400.

754
00:45:18,260 --> 00:45:20,820
You've been raising your grandkids for money?

755
00:45:20,820 --> 00:45:23,620
If I had to pay more, I'd get a professional.

756
00:45:23,630 --> 00:45:25,450
Why would I have you take care of them?

757
00:45:25,460 --> 00:45:27,390
And you won't stop nagging,

758
00:45:27,400 --> 00:45:29,310
making them sick and hurt.

759
00:45:29,320 --> 00:45:31,080
I can't help it if they get sick!

760
00:45:31,090 --> 00:45:34,280
It's because you don't pay attention!

761
00:45:34,300 --> 00:45:35,250
Come with me.

762
00:45:35,260 --> 00:45:37,150
- Man!
- I don't pay attention?

763
00:45:37,150 --> 00:45:39,610
I'm raising your kids for you and you say that?

764
00:45:39,630 --> 00:45:40,580
I can't believe this!

765
00:45:40,590 --> 00:45:42,180
You're worse than a mother in law!

766
00:45:42,190 --> 00:45:44,840
I worked my butt off raising her kids!

767
00:45:44,860 --> 00:45:46,950
And that's the thanks I get?

768
00:45:46,960 --> 00:45:49,640
Then take your kids and move out!

769
00:45:53,920 --> 00:45:56,110
Don't do that to your mother.

770
00:45:56,130 --> 00:45:59,080
You heard what she said.

771
00:45:59,090 --> 00:46:02,010
Having to live here is miserable enough,

772
00:46:02,030 --> 00:46:04,550
but she tells me to take my kids and move out.

773
00:46:04,550 --> 00:46:06,140
I thought you were upset, too.

774
00:46:06,150 --> 00:46:09,240
Just let it go. You told me that.

775
00:46:09,260 --> 00:46:11,320
Imagine how hard it must be for her.

776
00:46:11,320 --> 00:46:14,640
When the kids get hurt, don't blame mother.

777
00:46:15,190 --> 00:46:18,180
She was so worried that she cried.

778
00:46:18,190 --> 00:46:20,040
Even though they're my kids,

779
00:46:20,050 --> 00:46:22,410
it's hard to take care of them.

780
00:46:22,420 --> 00:46:24,540
You shouldn't just leave them to her.

781
00:46:25,230 --> 00:46:26,680
It's not like I'm doing nothing!

782
00:46:26,690 --> 00:46:28,540
I have a job!

783
00:46:28,550 --> 00:46:30,120
Mom said she'll take care of Jungji,

784
00:46:30,130 --> 00:46:31,310
so I can go out and make money.

785
00:46:31,320 --> 00:46:33,240
So why is she acting like this now?

786
00:46:34,030 --> 00:46:36,550
You should fix your work hours.

787
00:46:36,550 --> 00:46:39,080
You can't keep going to work in the evenings

788
00:46:39,090 --> 00:46:41,040
to come home late or early in the mornings.

789
00:46:41,050 --> 00:46:42,540
You have too many work dinners.

790
00:46:42,550 --> 00:46:43,910
You drink every night.

791
00:46:43,920 --> 00:46:45,720
You're a housewife.

792
00:46:45,730 --> 00:46:48,990
Why does that matter when I have a job?

793
00:46:49,000 --> 00:46:51,620
You work too, so how could you say that?

794
00:46:51,630 --> 00:46:55,390
When I go to work, I'm not a housewife.

795
00:46:55,400 --> 00:46:57,310
Do you hear her?

796
00:46:57,320 --> 00:47:00,620
I could just slap her on the mouth.

797
00:47:00,630 --> 00:47:03,190
Why didn't you follow them upstairs?

798
00:47:03,190 --> 00:47:04,640
I'm not crazy!

799
00:47:04,650 --> 00:47:07,240
She needs that.

800
00:47:07,260 --> 00:47:11,150
Oh, I wish Minjung were our son.

801
00:47:11,150 --> 00:47:13,880
A son like him would be so reliable.

802
00:47:16,730 --> 00:47:19,290
Why are you smiling like that?

803
00:47:19,300 --> 00:47:20,490
No reason.

804
00:47:24,050 --> 00:47:27,220
Wash them clean.
 Don't forget the corners.

805
00:47:27,230 --> 00:47:29,640
I don't want to have to do them again.

806
00:47:29,650 --> 00:47:32,810
Don't worry.
 I'm meticulous.

807
00:47:32,820 --> 00:47:34,620
Nice going.

808
00:47:36,030 --> 00:47:38,550
Mother, this is actually fun.

809
00:47:38,550 --> 00:47:41,580
I need to do this to be appreciated.

810
00:47:41,590 --> 00:47:44,850
What if your father saw you doing this?

811
00:47:44,860 --> 00:47:48,350
He'd say, "Good job! Good for you."

812
00:47:48,360 --> 00:47:51,690
This isn't right!
 Egh, hyo, hyo, hyo.

813
00:47:58,530 --> 00:47:59,750
Father.

814
00:48:01,460 --> 00:48:02,950
I'm sorry for all the trouble I caused.

815
00:48:02,960 --> 00:48:05,080
No, don't say that.

816
00:48:06,130 --> 00:48:09,150
We're actually pretty pleased.

817
00:48:09,150 --> 00:48:11,580
Couples need to fight sometimes, too.

818
00:48:13,920 --> 00:48:16,180
- Minjung.
 - Yes, father?

819
00:48:16,190 --> 00:48:20,080
It feels like you're really family now.

820
00:48:20,090 --> 00:48:23,810
My wife is so happy with you.

821
00:48:31,730 --> 00:48:33,580
You have to get married.

822
00:48:33,590 --> 00:48:36,810
I want to move out of this house with you.

823
00:48:36,820 --> 00:48:39,740
But nobody wants to marry me.

824
00:48:39,760 --> 00:48:41,750
Who is she?

825
00:48:41,760 --> 00:48:43,850
Semi real estate tycoon.

826
00:48:43,860 --> 00:48:49,020
It means she has lots of land or buildings.

827
00:48:49,030 --> 00:48:50,420
Is that true?

828
00:48:50,420 --> 00:48:53,610
You're in luck, then.

829
00:48:53,630 --> 00:48:57,520
I'll have to meet her to see if I am.

830
00:49:01,730 --> 00:49:02,910
Go inside. It's cold.

831
00:49:02,920 --> 00:49:06,340
